    <title>Protecting Americans from Drug Marketing Act</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-04-04T21:28:57Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2016-03-03</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <updateDate>2016-03-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Protecting Americans from Drug Marketing Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to deny a tax deduction for the cost of direct-to-consumer advertising of prescription drugs. The bill defines &quot;direct-to-consumer advertising&quot; as any dissemination by or on behalf of a sponsor of a prescription drug product of a prescription drug advertisement that is primarily targeted to the general public through: (1) publication in journals, magazines, other periodicals, and newspapers; (2) broadcasting through media such as radio, television, and telephone communication systems; and (3) dissemination on the Internet (including social media). </p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
